<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Ref #</p></th>
<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Assumption</p></th>
<th class=3D"highlight-#f4f5f7 confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vert=
ical-align: top;" data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7"><p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A01</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>&nbsp;Data sourcing for account listing / detail</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong>Current account listing data</strong> is sourced from <strong>1=
0x</strong></li>
<li><strong>Past account listing data</strong> (closing balance) is expecte=
d to be sourced from&nbsp;<strong>ATLAS</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Account detail view</strong> will source data from both <strong=
>10x and ATLAS</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Current account listing data</strong> and <strong>top section o=
f account detail</strong> are both sourced from <strong>10x</strong>, ensur=
ing consistency.</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A02</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Filtering requirement on account activity / transaction listing</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Amount filter / Debit filter will filter only transaction listing table=
.</li>
<li>time filter will have effect on=20
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Opening balance&nbsp;</li>
<li>Total debits</li>
<li>Total credits</li>
<li>Closing balance/Current balance</li>
<li>Transaction listing</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
A03</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Current date handling</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>if Current date (T) is selected for to date=20
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><s>Current balance (sourcing from 10x) will be displayed instead of Clo=
sing balance&nbsp;</s></li>
<li>Total debits / credits will be calculated ad-hoc by the instl Account t=
ransaction endpoint instead of retrieving from DynamoDB, since DynamoDB onl=
y holds pre-calculated data from the previous date. (T-1)</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
