<h3 id=3D"id-12.SD:PastaccountbalancesChannels-Constraints&amp;Dependencies=
">Constraints &amp; Dependencies</h3>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 364.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 372.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 480.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 361.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 184.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Ref #</st=
rong></p><p>[C-###, D-###]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Considera=
tions Type</strong></p><p>[Constraints, Dependencies]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Descripti=
on</strong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Notes</st=
rong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Date</str=
ong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-JIRAFEATURE-001=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><strong>Filtering and searching</strong> will continue to follow the <s=
trong>existing client-side approach</strong> due to <strong>DynamoDB limita=
tions</strong>, even if past data is sourced from ATLAS.</li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-JIRAFEATURE-002=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>To enable caching of past account data in Redis, orchestration must occ=
ur in the <strong>EXP layer</strong>.</li>
<li>This orchestration will merge:=20
<ul>
<li><strong>Current data</strong> from the <strong>10x/W1C arrangement endp=
oint</strong></li>
<li><strong>Past data</strong> from the <strong>ATLAS endpoint</strong></li=
>
</ul></li>
<li>A <strong>full list of data</strong> may need to be passed <strong>from=
 downstream to upstream</strong> to support paging and aggregation function=
ality.</li>
<li>The above approach <strong>will not be remediated</strong> until the <s=
trong>architecture roadmap/pattern</strong> has been clearly defined.</li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>D-JIRAFEATURE-001=
</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li><strong>ATLAS must support</strong> the necessary data structures and l=
ogic to provide:=20
<ul>
<li>Historical account closing balance data.</li>
<li>Daily total credit/debit.</li>
</ul></li>
<li><strong>Integration between 10x and ATLAS</strong> must ensure consiste=
nt data formatting and availability for both current and historical views.<=
/li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-12.SD:PastaccountbalancesChannels-KeyDecisions"><span>Key Deci=
sions</span></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped relative-table confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 89.=
1395%;">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 2.95459%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 21.5913%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 62.8472%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 8.97742%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 3.5796%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Ref</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Decision</th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Description</p>
</div></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Decision made by</p>
</div></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" scope=3D"col" class=3D"=
confluenceTh">Status</th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#001</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Endpoints alignment</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Meeting has been arranged on 5th Nov 2025 to confirm the below:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Confirmed whether accrual should be included in the Interest and Tax Su=
mmary endpoint or a separate resource/component. This aligns with the appro=
ach taken for the Overdraft feature in February.</li>
</ul>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Decided that closing and opening balances should remain attached to the=
 transaction listing as per the Past Account Balance ACD, or as a separate =
resource/component.</li>
</ul><p><br></p><p>The below has been discussed during the meeting:</p>
<ul>
<li><p><strong>Accrual Interest &amp; Tax Summary</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Introduce a new accrual resource/endpoint within the existing <code>gts=
-interest-tax-details</code> API component.</li>
<li>Customer and Staff portals will continue using the current <code>gts-in=
terest-tax-details</code> API for interest and tax summary.</li>
<li>A separate endpoint will return credit/debit accrual interest since the=
 last posting.</li>
<li>Change impacts Staff Portal overdraft feature in <strong>February</stro=
ng>.</li>
<li><strong>Action:</strong> Andrew to provide Swagger draft and ETA.</li>
</ul></li>
<li><p><strong>Transaction Totals (Debits/Credits)</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Amount filters <strong>will not</strong> apply to Total Debits/Total Cr=
edits because calculations occur at API level after ATLAS retrieval.</li>
<li>New endpoint will return Total Debits/Total Credits for a given time ra=
nge:=20
<ul>
<li><strong>Past data:</strong> Use pre-calculated ATLAS values.</li>
<li><strong>Current data:</strong> Calculate ad-hoc from ATLAS.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li><p><strong>Opening/Closing Balance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Additional data (opening/closing balance) will be attached to the <code=
>w1c arrangement</code> API.</li>
<li>Consideration: Should the arrangement endpoint fetch data from both <st=
rong>10x</strong> and <strong>ATLAS</strong>?</li>
<li>Future complexity expected when LMS and other features are added in <st=
rong>May</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Pending Decision:</strong> Confirm inclusion of opening/closing=
 balance in May release (Mel Jamieson to advise).</li>
</ul></li>
</ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Updates (17th Nov 2025):</strong></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>It's been agreed between Robin, Ave and Andrew that:=20
<ul>
<li>We will build for 10x now rather than waiting for the Trading Bank (TB)=
 solution.</li>
<li>Current analysis indicates this approach will remain compatible with TB=
, minimizing the risk of future rework.</li>
<li>Opening and closing balance data will be <strong>attached to the w1c ar=
rangement API</strong>.</li>
<li>Past data will be sourced from ATLAS, while current data will come from=
 10x.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>This design supports immediate delivery and positions us well for futur=
e enhancements.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M037818" =
href=3D"/display/~M037818" data-linked-resource-id=3D"7244962" data-linked-=
resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Stuart Murdoch</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M058573" =
href=3D"/display/~M058573" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1125291984" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Ave Cahyadi</a>&nbsp;<br><a c=
lass=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M062050" href=3D=
"/display/~M062050" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1515690289" data-linked-reso=
urce-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"=
https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Andrew Suduk</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M065552" =
href=3D"/display/~M065552" data-linked-resource-id=3D"2096187630" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Rajeev Ranjan</a></p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M051940" =
href=3D"/display/~M051940" data-linked-resource-id=3D"710494799" data-linke=
d-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-u=
rl=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Robin Fitzgerald</a> &nbsp;</p=
>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Closed</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
#002</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Deferral of Redis Implementation for Past Account Feature</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<ul>
<li>The Past Account feature (May release) involves retrieving opening/clos=
ing balances from ATLAS for multiple accounts.</li>
<li>Ave recommended using <strong>Redis cache</strong> on the EXP API layer=
 to reduce intensive <strong>DynamoDB calls</strong>.</li>
<li>Concerns were raised that Redis would introduce additional complexity a=
t the API layer, and its benefit may be limited due to dynamic account/date=
 combinations and entitlement-driven data.</li>
</ul><p><strong>Decision:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Redis implementation will be deferred</strong> until there is a=
 clear need, such as:=20
<ul>
<li>Performance issues identified during load testing, or</li>
<li>Significant increase in data volume or customer base.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul><p><strong>Next Steps:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Monitor performance as user volumes scale and revisit Redis implementat=
ion if required.</li>
<li>Validate decision with the&nbsp;<strong>Data Team</strong>.</li>
</ul><p><br></p><p><strong>27th Nov: </strong>Aligned with Umesh (Data team=
) =E2=80=94 no concerns on ATLAS performance. Redis implementation is expec=
ted to boost performance and poses no technical issues. Channel to decide b=
ased on actual needs, considering user volume and findings from performance=
 tests.</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"F079288" =
href=3D"/display/~F079288" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1415102363" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Melinda Jamieson</a></p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M058573" =
href=3D"/display/~M058573" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1125291984" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Ave Cahyadi</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M064401" =
